journal_entry: Was married at home in evening by William Rand Esqr.
About home at work jobbing.
Work about home.
To work in shop.
Work in shop.
Work in shop wrote a letter to N H Higgins Ellsworth one to Jordan & Blake
Wrote a will for Benj Rand
Unwell staid in house.
Went to C. J. Guptills first time out since sat.
Went up the stream to pile up wood.
Cleaning road and and cutting wood on home lot.
Whites landing cutting wood.
Cutting wood Whites Landing
Laying shop floor
Work in shop
Cutting wood stopping at camp
Came home from camp read a letter from Joseph Bunker & Emery
work in shop reed a letter from CC Burrill Ellsworth one from George N Loomis
Work in shop
building lathe in shop
Went to C Isles to buy boat in A. G. Brooks took dinner on board on supper & lodging at Joseph Bunkers
Came home in A G Brook very moderate all day
work on lathe
unwell unable to work
Breakfast dinner & tea with E Kingsley
Took breakfast with A Robinson came home
Cutting wood at the door went to lodge of Good Templar in Evening
Commenced work in Life Ins. with CC Burrill
The Same as the day before
Went to Ellsworth to see Mr Burrill and back home
Breakfast with H D Ciombs dinner with Albert Joy wrote letter to CC Burrill came home went to Lodge of Good Templars
Went to I Hammonds to see Dr. Stockman
same as yesterday
Went to District meeting found it to be illegal went to Lodge of Good Templars in evening staid to A. J. Gerrishes all night
work in shop on windmill
Went to W. Gouldsboro in the Insurance business took dinner with E Kingsley tea with H. Young Lodging Wm Joys
Breakfast at Wm. Joys dinner at Same Woods wrote letter to CC Burrill came home
Staid at home
Read letter from CC Burrill went to West Gouldsboro in the Ins. Busi took tea with Edward Kingsley Lodging with Samuel Wood
Went to Prospect Harbor with CC Burrill took dinner with H D Coombs came home
Went to Prospect Harbor with CC Burrill took dinner with H D Coombs came home
Went to Prospect Harbor and back.
Reed letter from Geo W Tracy. Evening went to Lodge of Good Templars
Work in shop
Work in shop in forenoon afternoon went floundering
Went to Turtle Isle. Eve went to Lodge recd letter from CC Burrill & Hale & Emery
breakfast with E. Young dinner with John Wood Supper & Lodging with Hannah Goodwin
Breakfast wtih Hannah G dinner with Stephen Kingsly reed letter from Hale Emery one from CC burrill came home
Work in shop on windmill
work on shop finished windmill
went on Turtle Isle got pogrichum
went to Seal Cove in Same Knight dinner on board supper & Lodging John Smallidge
breakfast at Mrs Finleys went to C Isles work on mermaid dinner supper Loding with Joseph Bunker
Work in shop went to Lodge of G. Templars
Stormy work in shop making blocks for boat
Staid at home
work in shop
breakfast and dinner at Thomas Smallidges
painted boat took dinner at J Smallidges reed letter from CC Burrill went to Lodge
Went to Hancock got 6540 lbs lobsters
Came home in boat
Took 3900 lbs lobster to factory went to Lamoine
Took 5400 lbs lobsters to factory
Carried 6425 lbs lobsters to factory went up Skillings river
Took 6400 lbs lobster to factory. went Crabtrees nook
staid at home
Carried 1800 lbs lobsters to factory went to Lamoine
Took 3960 lbs lobsters to factory
Got 3675 lbs lobsters went to Hancock
Got 1500 lbs went to Hulls cove got 1755 lbs went to factory and back to Hancock
Took 1043 lbs lobsters to factory went to West Gouldsboro took dinner with John Shaw got some plank and went home
Went to Sunday School concert in evening
Took 2132 lbs lobster to factory, went to Jordans river
Breakfast at home went up Skillings river
Took 5600 lbs lobster to factory went to Sullivan
Took 2913 lbs lobsters to factory went to Hancock
Took 1720 lbs to factory
Married Mr Nriah G Bunker and Mys. Hannah C Bunker went to Lamoine in boat hired team went to Ellsworth Lodging with Chas C Burrill
breakfast with CC Burill attended Probate Bount proved the will of Benj Rand dinner at city Hotel supper and Lodging on board boat at Lamoine
Took 1993 lbs lobsters to factory went to Hancock
staid at home
Took 2437 lbs lobsters to factory went to Lamoine
breakfast at home went up Skillings river
Took 4800 lbs lobsters to factory came home in boat Supper & Lodging at home
acknowledged deed for C Stevens and deeded all my right of the Estate to Jamie accept house shed and land in front to Isaacs lime went to Lodge of Good Templars
Took 1260 lbs lobster to factory went to Lamoine
Went to Hancock got 5400 lbs lobster. and walked home. after tea
hired C Stevens team took wife went to Ellsworth dinner Supper & Lodging at city Hotel
breakfast at city hotel dinner at W. Gouldsboro S. Woods supper at home Lodging ?focty
went to Hancock got 1115 lbs lobsters came home in boat went to G. T. Lodge in evening
went to Hancock got 1115 lbs lobsters came home in boat went to G. T. Lodge in evening
Took 800 lbs lobsters to factory went up Skillings river
Took 3580 lbs lobsters to factory walked home took supper and Lodging
Went up to Skillings river
Took boat on beach cleaned bottom went to Lodge of Good Templars
Took 2675 lbs lobsters to factory went up Skillings river
Took 1000 lbs lobsters to factory settles up reed pay
went to lobster factory after caned strawberrys reed letter from G. W. Tracy went to Lodge of G. Templars
Rainy finished making mast for mermaid went to Lodge of G. Templars
Wind South Made a litter for boat finished haying hauled in 16 cocks went to Temperance lecture in evening Mr Hansenn & Mrs Fremeh
Work on boat cauling painting went to Lodge of Good Templars
Cutting at the door in forenoon Reed letter from A. Martin Millbridge
Left home for Rockland in forenoon calm & foggy anckored in Cranberry Isle harbor at night went in the boat mermaid
Wind from E.N.E. to S.S.W. rainy and foggy. Went from Cranberry Isle to Buckle Island
The wind all around the compass very moderate Left Deer Isle for Rockland arrived in Rockland at 9 P.M.
The wind E. in forenoon afternoon S. and foggy ordered fore sail made for boat tea at Wm Woods
Waiting for chance to go home
Sailed from Rockland for home the wind North arrived at 9 oclock PM
Staid at home all day
rainy build Coal bin wrote letter to Hale & Emery Ellworth Me.
hauled home 3 loads coal cut down a piece of oats Acknowledge deed for N. Hammond
Commenced to finish the inside of James Bourgetts house work in forenoon in afternoon went to W. Gouldsboro to nominate Can. for Represe Took tea at E. Kingsly
Work on James Bourgetts house making door frames and window frames dinner at Abner Tracys
Getting out door and window Casings mop boards &c dinner to Abner Tracys as Usual
Furrowed over head and studied of the sorms wrote letter to C C Burrill dinner as usual. went to Political lecture gone one hour and 15 min.
Breakfast at Thomas Smallidges Went to meeting in forenoon and afternoon
Work on James Bourgetts house lathing dinner at Abner Tracys
Lathing cookroom dinner as usual while to work on house
Made sink mantle piece & went to Lodge of Good Templars
Laid the floors through the house bought cloth to make pants
Finished the house throughought at noon engaged C Stevens team for tomorrow
Came home in forenoon afternoon went up the shore to work for Damon Sargent Engaged to board wills Calvin Hammond while to work on said house
Staid at home unwell
Quite sick took sweat at night
Sent for Dr Johnson stormy did not come
Pretty low with fever reed letters of administation of the estate of B Rand
Reed letter from Chas. C. Burrill
Dr Johnson came left more medicine
NA
NA
NA
NA
On the mending hand several came in to see me.
Wrote letter to H. M. Soule. one to mary Moore. one to Capt. Thomas Smallidge
Wrote letter to Byron Welsh
making Tolers heads
Went to Thomas Smallidge in afternoon my weight 130
Work in shop
Work about Home sent to Boston after Parlor stove
appraised the Real Estate Goods and Chattels of the Estate of B Rand
Gathered turnips and beets wrote letter to Hale and Emery
Took Hayrick apart put it away done some chored up for fall
About home went to the Lodge installed officers had supper
Went to Election dinner at the factory Supper & Lodging at C Hammonds
Find lathe to drill Iron and work in shop
Went to Turtle Island gunning Reed letters from Hale & Emery Jordan & Blake Perley & Russel G. W. Tracy Went to Lodge
Went gunning on Egg Rock got 6 birds afternoon bought 2 bbls apples
Went to West Gouldsboro with potatoes to ship to Rockland
Started for Portland in the scow Virgin got dinner at Enoch Stanleys
Got to Bass Harbor
Laid in Bass Harbor wrote letter to my wife
Went to Buckle Island
Went to Rockland arrived at 9 P.M.
Hauled in the wharf
had watch clearned bought screw plate took curs? for Rockland arrived at 6. supper on board
Started for home in vessel got to Deer Isle
arrived at home at 4 P.M.
Hauling home brick shingles and boards from S Guptills wharf went to Lodge. Reed letter from CC Burrill
Work in shop turning and repairing furniture
Repairing and setting up stove in harbor reed $ 8.00 of P B Fuss
Work in shop reed letter from Hale & Emery went to Lodge of G.T. reed letter from Hale & Emery
Commenced laying floor in harbor
Took tea at Capt Thos Smallidge Stoped eve.
Hauled the boat up to the bank for the winter
Work in shop stove windmill to pieces running with great speed
Staid at home all day
Work in shop. evening went to Christmas tree
Took tea at Thomas Smallidge
